article.description: Seth Dugan scored a career-high 17 points with 10 rebounds to lead seven Western Michigan players into double figures in a 101-59 defeat of NAIA Marygrove College on Saturday night.
article.headline: Western Michigan defeats NAIA Marygrove College 101-59
article.linkText: Western Michigan defeats NAIA Marygrove College 101-59
article.story: KALAMAZOO, Mich. -- Seth Dugan scored a career-high 17 points with 10 rebounds to lead seven Western Michigan players into double figures in a 101-59 defeat of NAIA Marygrove College on Saturday night. Dugan, a 7-foot freshman, made 6 of 12 field goals and had four assists. All 10 Western Michigan players scored in the game, and all of the starters finished with eight points or better. The Broncos (5-5) led by as much as 41-9 with 6:38 left in the first half and built a 35-point lead, 58-23, by halftime. Tucker Haymond scored 15 points, Kellen McCormick and Josh Davis had 12 each, and the trio of Anthony Avery Jr. Taylor Perry and Bryce Moore scored 10 each. Tyler Sykes led the Mustangs with 21 points. The Broncos owned the boards 52-34 and made 13 steals with eight players having at least one, and Davis with five.
